{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Only require child maintenance from fathers listed on birth certificate",
        "additional_details": "This would help to prevent mothers who refuse to voluntarily add the father to the birth certificate from seeking to claim child maintenance from a man who may not be the father. It would also prevent men who dispute the fatherhood and don\u2019t feel they should have to pay maintenance from having to pay for a DNA test to prove it (could be hundreds of pounds).",
        "background": "The Government should change the rules for child maintenance, so that mothers can only apply for child maintenance when the birth father is listed on the birth certificate.",
